### FHIR Patient — note: FHIR routes are VERSION_NEUTRAL, so they are served at
### /fhir/R4/... WITHOUT the /v1 prefix. {{host}} includes /v1, so these requests
### target the host root explicitly.

@fhirBase = http://127.0.0.1:4201/fhir/R4

### Create a Patient
POST {{fhirBase}}/Patient
Content-Type: application/fhir+json
Authorization: Bearer {{at_token}}

{
  "resourceType": "Patient",
  "active": true,
  "identifier": [
    { "system": "urn:hsm:mrn", "value": "MRN-0001", "use": "official" }
  ],
  "name": [{ "use": "official", "family": "Doe", "given": ["Jane"] }],
  "gender": "female",
  "birthDate": "1990-01-01"
}

### Read a Patient by id (replace the id with one returned by Create)
GET {{fhirBase}}/Patient/REPLACE_WITH_ID
Authorization: Bearer {{at_token}}

### Search by identifier (system|value) → searchset Bundle
GET {{fhirBase}}/Patient?identifier=urn:hsm:mrn|MRN-0001
Authorization: Bearer {{at_token}}

### Search by bare identifier value
GET {{fhirBase}}/Patient?identifier=MRN-0001
Authorization: Bearer {{at_token}}

### Invalid create — missing resourceType → 422 OperationOutcome
POST {{fhirBase}}/Patient
Content-Type: application/fhir+json
Authorization: Bearer {{at_token}}

{
  "gender": "female"
}
